name: stillwater-wildlife-management-area-annual-water-management-plan-c3eaf
notes: The primary goal of the annual water plan is to set a strategy for the most  efficient use of the available water delivered to Stillwater WMA. For all practical purposes, Fallon NWR no longer receives sufficient water down the Carson River to maintain any quality wetlands. Now that the flood waters are receding we will have to deal with full impacts of the new Operating Criteria and Procedures (OCAP). It looks like we will receive 40,000 AF. This is the 1987 plan.
